<form id="project-add" enctype="multipart/form-data" method="post" action="/projects/wizard">
    
    <div class="wizard-tip wizard-general-tip project-definition-wizard-tip">
        <h1 class="wizard-tip-title">Defining Your Project</h1>
        <p>We will step you through the process of providing a clear
           articulation of what your project sets out to solve. This is intended
           to give your audience an understanding of the rationale for the
           project.</p>
        
        <h2>More Information</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#">Problem vs. Project/Issue</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!--+ First you have to figure out what you want to do.  This bring up the
        | question: how did you land on the site.  Let's address a few ways:
        | 
        | 1) You did a google search for "how do i start a neighborhood watch
        |    association" or someting.
        | 2) You were on an issue reporting site (like Kajoo) and you reported
        |    an issue or saw an issue that you wanted addressed.  It said that
        |    you could check whether anyone was working on the issue at the city
        |    heroes site, so you came here to look for the issue.
        | 3) You heard about it through some advertising campaign and want to 
        |    plan a national night out.
        | 4) You ask (on city how) how to get the city to clean up a vacant lot
        |    and someone recommends that you come to city hero and try to get it
